Just like our scientists build on the findings of Newton and Einstein, you can learn from people who have done what you wanna do. 

The only problem is that today, most people don't have the freedom to change what they wanna change.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '1. People come and go and that's OK Your best friends can become strangers and strangers can become your best friends- and that happens for a reason: In life, you would always have the people around you that help you get to the next stop on your journey. Some will stay with you until the end and some only are companions for a time. @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '2. Your diet isn't just what you eat A healthy body and a healthy mind go hand-in-hand. To be truly healthy, watch your diet, but also what you read, who you talk and what you think. to @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '3. You can't please everyone if you want to be happy Your mental health and happiness always go 1st. Only if you're at your best you can help others be happy and sometimes that means letting people down. @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '4. Don't let rejection become self-rejection Everyone will face rejection in their life sooner or later. But even if somebody rejects you you still have value as a person. Don't define yourself by someone else's "no." @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '5. Your past doesn't define your future Even if you had a rough childhood, and life dealt you a bad hand, this doesn't mean that you can't change your future. In fact, you can now choose to react differently, to feel differently and to live differently. @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '6. You won't find happiness in other people's dreams If you only work to achieve goals that society says you are supposed to want you will never be happy. It's perfectly okay to have dreams that almost no one agrees with. It's perfectly okay to work on something no one understands as long as it fulfils you. @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says '7. Everything is up to to you It's uncomfortable to accept that you can take responsibility for everything in your life. But taking ownership gives you the power to truly change your life in any way you want. Never blame others for your misfortune but rather take action to change what you don't want @basharjkatou'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 14, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. But not every business is good for beginner entrepreneurs because building a business takes some skill. So here's a recommendation for a good, beginner- friendly skill barrier: @basharjkatou'.

There are only two options in life : 

You either love what you do or you don't.

Both are OK as long as you know what you're doing…

Because you either continue what you're doing because you love it or you change what you do because you hate it.

Most people get stuck on how to change what they don't like.

That's why so many people start a business because today, a business is more than just an income stream. A business is a way to solve your and other people's problems and get paid for it on top.

It's a fantastic way to change your life and make an impact in the world. There's only one problem :

Most people have no idea how business works, and lose everything they had trying to build a business that failed.

That's why I often recommend that you 

follow 👉@bjkuniversity 
follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity

Because they teach you how to build an Amazon FBA business.

Customer service, storage, advertising, shipping, handling, billing, invoicing, refunds, returns, hiring and managing a team,  Amazon does it all for you.

node.text:
Now’s your time: JOIN BJK-UNIVERSITY ON A 100% SCHOLARSHIP AND GET $3,000 PRODUCT BUDGET

To apply for the scholarship, here’s what you need to do:

Follow @basharjkatou & @bjkuniversity
Like this post
Comment under this post why you deserve the scholarship
Share this post in your story and tag @bjkuniversity

This is a two-round selection. We will choose 20 people among all applicants on our Instagram page and Bashar J Katou’s Instagram page who will advance into the next round. 

You will get a DM if you advanced into the next round.

From the 20 chosen applicants we will choose the one who we can see succeed the most.

Remember: 

You’ll get full access to BJK-University for life on a 100% scholarship.
Once you found a product, you’ll get $3,000 as a budget to source and test products, PPC, logo, etc.
Only one person will be accepted
I will personally onboard you

But once you’re in, you gotta:

Post at least once a week about your progress in our facebook group
Visit at least one live QnA call per week
Visit at least one of the Orientation calls
Do all the assignments exactly as instructed

Too much? Don’t apply.

Business isn’t a baby daycare. And if you can’t do the minimum, you’re not fit for building a business.

I won’t give it to someone who won’t finish the course.
I’ll give this to someone who is desperate to change their lives and has such a strong drive that they’ll give everything to make this work.

PS- You can double your chances by applying on @bjkuniversity’s post as well!

PPS: Don‘t wait too long. We will choose the first 20 people among all applicants who will advance into the next round within 72 hours. 

If you are in the next round you will get a DM on Instagram. So watch out for it, because you’ll have only 24 hours to respond or you will lose your spot.

After the 24 hours you have to respond are over, the winner will be announced within 72 hours on @bjkuniversity and @basharjkatou

Per Instagram rules, this promotion is in no way sponsored, administered, or associated with Instagram, Inc. By entering, entrants confirm that they are 21+ years of age, release Instagram of responsibility, and agree to Instagram’s terms of use.

node.text:
Everyone can start a business but many people will do it wrong.  Why?

Because most people underestimate how much it takes to just come up with a business idea, much less makes it profitable.

All these fake online gurus make it look like starting a business is like picking up a new hobby and seeing where it goes.

 But this is just crazy because business takes money to start, it takes effort to start. If you don't take it seriously and educate yourself properly, not only will you fail but you might even lose everything you have.

Perform surgery on someone without proper training would you? So don't try starting a business being completely blind about its risks and dangers. 

This is especially true for Amazon FBA:

Because Amazon makes it so simple to run the business it's easy to think it would also be easy, but it's not.

You still need to find the right products, find the right manufacturer, plan shipping times and much more.

On your own this is a nightmare:

How would you know what to prioritize, how would you know where to focus on? 

If nobody tells you what to look out for, how do you deal with sudden obstacles and problems?

That's why education is important.

I tried skipping this and ONE mistake alone cost me 7k…

So be smarter than I was.

follow 👉 @bjkuniversity
follow 👉 @bjkuniversity
follow 👉 @bjkuniversity

And learn how to start a business the right way!

node.text:
Want unbeatable confidence? Then this is for you

Confidence is weird. 

You're born with it (how else would you try to walk after failing 67 times an hour for months?)

then you lose confidence because of people crushing it…

And then you get to relearn it later in life.

If you ask me it makes more sense to just trust yourself don't you agree?

Often, starting something you never failed at before helps.

It's new so you don't expect to succeed  ä(removes pressure) immediately…

But you also kinda expect failure at first and you're cool with it.

That's why starting a business is like therapy for many people.

Try it out and see for yourself how you feel!

For some inspiration

follow 👉 @bjkuniversity
follow 👉 @bjkuniversity
follow 👉 @bjkuniversity

And they'll show you how to start a business you'll be proud of!

May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #1 Gain Clarity Regularly Clarity helps finding your purpose and vision and exposes any obstacles in your way Το find clarity, take 10 minutes a day to write down your goals and learnings of the day Unplug from social media for at least 1h before you do this to Calm your mind first!'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 13, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #2 Practice Gratitude Gratitude is the natural enemy of anxiety, fear, and depression and makes your life brighter: Το practice it, write down five things everyday that you are grateful for. It might be hard at first but you'll get used to it and feel amazing! Stop comparing yourself to others to make sure you don't lose this!'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 13, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #3 Stay accountable 97% of the world don't achieve their goals because they just fall off the bandwagon. Accountability protects you from that. Get a partner to hold you accountable for your goals, and agree on a punishment if you fail or a reward if you succeed! Don't allow even one slip up or you're back to square one again!'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 13, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #4 Practice faith Anything in life that's currently seen as "a fact" can change in an instant. "Humans can't fly, 'the sun goes around the earth," "cars will never replace horses"... Those were facts until they weren't Faith helps you achieve your goal even if the current "facts" say you can't do it'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 13, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #5 Invest time to grow daily Daily growth makes you feel accomplished, worthy, and better than yesterday. It's very rewarding. Read 10 pages of a self- development book a day Take a course every now and then Watch ted talks and visit seminars If you feel down and worthless you probably didn't grow enough yet today'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 13, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #6 See both your strengths and weaknesses It's easy to focus on your shortcomings and forget what you excel at... But your weaknesses help you develop new skills and guide you to people who complete you See weaknesses as growth opportunities!'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 13, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #7 Create something impactful Low confidence often comes from feeling like you or your life don't matter If you create something many people enjoy you'll feel better than ever. You could craft things and sell them create a charity or start a business that makes people's lives better better'.

Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 13, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity.
